-- Guess quarterly profit rises
-- 
-- Tue Jun 5, 2007 5:41pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/05/us-guess-results-idUSBNG33594420070605

 

 (Reuters) - Clothes and accessories retailer Guess? Inc. ( GES.N ) posted quarterly earnings that beat analysts' expectations by a wide margin, driven by double-digit revenue growth across all of its businesses. 

 The company reported first-quarter net earnings of $35.5 million, or 38 cents a share, compared with $20.7 million, or 23 cents a share, for the recast quarter ended April 29, 2006. Revenue rose 42.3 percent to $377.9 million in the quarter. Analysts were expecting the company to earn 29 cents a share, before special items, on revenue of $331.6 million, according to Reuters Estimates. Sales at both European and Asian businesses rose 77 percent from the year-ago period. Licensing segment net revenue increased 41.5 percent to $20.3 million. The company, which operates 336 retail stores in the United States and Canada, said sales at stores open at least a year in North America were up 13.6 percent. Looking ahead, the company expects second-quarter earnings of 31 cents to 33 cents a share and revenue to range between $335 million and $345 million. Analysts expect earnings of 27 cents a share on revenue of $308.5 million for the quarter. Shares of the company were up about 6 percent in late electronic trading after closing at $47.42 on the New York Stock Exchange. (Reporting by Dilipp S. Nag and Saumyadeb Chakrabarty in Bangalore)